'''''Baby John''''' is a 2024 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[action thriller film]] directed by [[Kalees]] that serves as a remake of [[Atlee (director)|Atlee]]'s 2016 Tamil film ''[[Theri (film)|Theri]]''. The film stars [[Varun Dhawan]] in the title role, alongside [[Keerthy Suresh]] (in her first Hindi film), [[Wamiqa Gabbi]], Zara Zyanna and [[Jackie Shroff]]. It is produced under [[Jio Studios]], Cine1 Studios, Vipin Agnihotri Films and A for Apple Studios. The film follows Sathya Verma, a former cop, who goes undercover as Baby John to protect his daughter from a past enemy.

The film was officially announced in July 2023 under the tentative title ''VD18'',{{efn|Dhawan's 18th film as leading actor}} and the official title was revealed in February 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Varun Dhawan Announces 'Biggest Action Entertainer' VD18 With Jawan Director Atlee |url=https://www.zoomtventertainment.com/bollywood/varun-dhawan-announces-biggest-action-entertainer-vd18-with-jawan-director-atlee-bollywood-news-entertainment-news-article-101436651 |access-date=10 January 2024 |website=Zoom TV |language=en |archive-date=10 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240110225133/https://www.zoomtventertainment.com/bollywood/varun-dhawan-announces-biggest-action-entertainer-vd18-with-jawan-director-atlee-bollywood-news-entertainment-news-article-101436651 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Principal photography]] held in [[Mumbai]] and [[Kerala]] commenced in August 2023 and ended in October 2024. The film has music composed by [[Thaman S]], with cinematography by Kiran Koushik and editing by [[Ruben (film editor)|Ruben]]. 

''Baby John'' was theatrically released on 25 December 2024, coinciding with [[Christmas]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Baby John: Varun Dhawan, Keerthy Suresh's Action-Thriller Postponed From May 31st |url=https://www.msn.com/en-in/entertainment/bollywood/baby-john-varun-dhawan-keerthy-sureshs-action-thriller-postponed-from-may-31st/ar-BB1lAzg9 |website=www.msn.com |publisher=support@india.com |access-date=18 May 2024}}</ref> The film received mixed reviews from critics.

